history.content:
Fall enrollment policies are described here: http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml  CS70 in fall currently has 35 students enrolled out of a projected 620 student enrollment.

Perhaps you are talking about trying to get into the summer offering of CS70?   If so, we will try to continue to expand the course pending being able to hire enough qualified TAs but we can't guarantee that you will be able to be enrolled. In fact, that is exactly what a waitlist means -- that we are not able to promise that you will be able to take that class even though we wish we could.

children.subject: It's an example. Neither Fall 13 nor Spring 15 would give you specific direction at this moment since you are signing up for F15 classes.
Can you update it to F15? A current date is more helpful to student, and the old date makes it look like the department forgot to update the date to this semester.

Come on.  You're making me despair about your generation which I promised not to do when I started working at Cal.

The intention is to make the department look like we believe that students bright enough to be admitted to UC Berkeley might be able to go the the UC Berkeley homepage and type into the search engine something to the effect of "telebears calendar fall 15" and go to any of the top results and find when telebears phase II ends.

I'm going to go cry in my coffee and then I'll request that it be updated.

Thank you for updating it. The outdated date made the EECS department look unprofessional but Michael-David's answer here really tops that. Wow, I did not expect that kind of a response to my suggestion.

history.content: I'm number 7 on the cs70 waitlist and I noticed it said on schedule.berkeley.edu that all the spots were filled up. Will the class be expanded so I can get in? I was wondering because I have decide what classes to take for fall 2015 soon and I wanted to know if I can trust in getting 70. Thanks.
